manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: ComfySure Wedge Cushion Relieves Pain While Driving: The ultimate Therapeutic Auto Seat Cushion that relieves hemorrhoids pain, pressure ulcers, prostatitis pain, pregnancy pain, childbirth pain, postpartum pain, and lower back pain. Relieves pressure on the pelvic, coccyx, tailbone, legs, and hip bones while driving on the long roads. Premium Quality Memory Foam: High-density contoured memory foam molds into an ergonomic streamlining and shapes according to your body. Therapeutic, the perfect consistency, not too firm, and won’t flatten out. This pillow is made to support up to 500 pounds. Versatile Uses: The ideal back pain reliever for people that sit for a long period of time. Can also be used to boost your height while driving and to easily see over the steering wheel for safer driving. Awesome support for office chairs, car seat chairs, wheelchairs, gaming chair, executive chair, sofa, couch, cars seat SUV seats, truck seats & recliner seats. Portable and convenient for traveling! Improves Spinal Alignment & Posture: Promotes a healthy vibrant posture for lower back pain sufferers. Doctors & chiropractors recommended lumbar cushion for pregnancy, post-partum, hip surgery recovery, piriformis, numbness on the lower back, lumbosacral spondylitis, hemorrhoids & fibromyalgia. Removable Machine Washable Cover: A washable pillow cover allows you to keep your pillow fresh and clean. Simply remove the cover and place it in the washing machine to have your pillow looking new. Product Dimensions: Dimensions: 13.8”X15.8”X3.1". Not too bulky yet large enough for most body types. The Ideal Get Well Gift: Awesome idea for business gift, office gifts, holiday gift & back surgery recovery gift. reviews.reviewText: Helpful for making driving more comfortable

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Seat cushion for the car
reviews.reviewText: It is firm and holds up to to maintain posture and comfort. I like the boost in height, as the drivers seat sits low and now I can see over the front hood.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Helps my back
reviews.reviewText: The wedge support does help my back. I placed it on the small computer chair that I use at my desktop computer desk. The wedge would have to be a little less thick in depth for it to be more comfortable to me. I kept it and I am using it anyway.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Comfortably firm with perfectly tapered shape
reviews.reviewText: I chose this one because it is narrow enough for my car seat + thick enough to elevate me, keeping my knees level with or below my hip line, for optimal lumbar spine comfort. It's tapered nicely so my legs aren't also elevated - just my 'posterior' is. Happy with how firm it WAS and that my lower back wasn't tense & achy after driving. Non-slip grip on the bottom holds it in place really well when I'm getting into/out of my car. The problem... I'm in my car only 2 or 3 days weekly and 2 hours on each day, yet in less than 2 months it's noticeably less firm and therefore thinner. I'm 5'9" & 135 lbs so my weight or center of gravity isn't to blame. Don't want to have to buy another but will have to soon at this rate! However I won't buy this one again.Size, shape, design, fabric: 5 stars / longevity: 1 star

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This works for me!
reviews.reviewText: I’ve been looking for a cushion that was higher in the back and lower in the front. This works great. It allows me to sit high enough to see while driving, yet keeps my legs and feet at an angle that they can reach the pedals.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A driving necessity!
reviews.reviewText: I have issues with lower-right back pain and it is made worse when I'm sitting in the car using my right leg to drive. I decided to give this pillow a try and it has been a life saver over the last year! A 30 min trip used to be unbearable. This pillow allows me to drive for 2+ hours comfortably! It helps by putting extra cushion under my hamstrings and also elevating my hips. 10/10.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I am not an aesthetic, but like this
reviews.reviewText: OK, so I was a little hesitant to buy this product because of the reviewer who said something to the effect of "perfect if you are an aesthetic and want to sit on a rock." That review seriously cracked me up. Yes, this thing is firm, but I like it. Iʻm not an aesthetic, but rode street bikes for many years with a thin seat. You sit on your sit bones and its fine. With this, its the same concept. I got this because my 2020 4runner seats are ridiculous- tilted so your knees are raised up and you are forced to sit in a seat the shape of a half-closed laptop. Even with the seat adjusted as level as possible, it was so uncomfortable. This cushion makes it do-able. This cushion is softer in the summer and harder in the winter until it warms up. It stays put and does not slide around, even when you scoot over it to step down out of the vehicle. I have used it for 5,000 miles and its still like new.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Nicely made and works for my needs, but it is alittle small.

Love my new Car seat cushion , the wedge works perfectly, helps support my lower back from back pain. Non slip helps it stay in place. My second cushion arrived today. One is for my car and the other is for home. I love the comfort of just sitting on this helpful cushion, if you have lower back problems I highly recommend this seat cushion. I sit a lot of time at my kitchen island bar ( just paying bills etc. on line ) and it works perfectly for me on a bar chair.

Demasiado pequeño inclusive para mi que me considero una persona delgada (1.75m, 73Kg) no se como las reseñas que dicen que esta muy bien lo usan seria necesario 2 de estos cojines para cubrir toda el area del asiento, ademas que es muy delgado y el conjin en si NUNCA llego a llenar la funda siempre se veia aguada!
Dose not slide around on the seat of my car and is comfortable to sit on.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on November 12, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This replaces a similar very old wedge I had been using. It is firm and fits into my car seat (which has sport wrap around seats) perfectly. It is firm and it means I can have the seat set lower to easily use the pedals and have the steering wheel lower without my knee touching the steering column but still have a good view. I am 5’ 4”. A comfortable driving position is assured.
